The paper deals with designing mechanisms for incentivizing users to upload high-quality content on user-generated-content (UGC) websites. This falls under the domain of game theory (cs.GT) as it involves designing mechanisms that incentivize users to act in a certain way. The problem is formulated as a linear program with bounded and increasing variables, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms to find the optimal mechanism, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with maximizing gross product, which is a topic in economics, suggesting that it could also fall under the category of electronic commerce (cs.EC).
